HIP: Homogenization of IMEGIN Photometry 
========================================
HIP is a multi-wavelength homogenization framework, with support for
error propagation. 


Install
-------
HIP is compatible with Linux and MacOS systems. For Windows users, we
recommend using WSL2. HIP is compatible with Python >= 3.8. To install
a local version, clone this repository, create a pyenv virtual
environment, install the required dependencies, create your pipeline, 
and run:

> git clone https://gitlab.com/jctdrs/pipeline.git
> python -m venv venv
> pip install -r requirements.txt
> python main.py --file config.yml

Documentation
-------------
Find the HIP documentation and guides to build pipelines here:
https://jctdrs.github.io/software/hip.html 
